<br>
Shadow Haven<br>
Shadow Haven is very very neat.  I believe this is how cities in Everquest *should* be.  Its so far away from the designs of Freeport and Qeynos and even Thurgadin.  The only &quot;city&quot; I actually half liked before was Fironie Vie, but this city takes the cake.  If they had done this kind of design for the underground city of Neriak I would have been an inky who never left home.<br>
<br>
I spent 1 and a half hours getting lost looking for the cleric spell vendor guy...and I enjoyed every second (except when I kept zoning into the Bazaar, Echo Caverns, etc by accident).  I was upset a few vendors didn't seem to like me (what did I ever do to you, moon man who won't have anything to do with sexy high elf men!?!) but still, the city has it all and more! I wish it was above ground, but maybe there is another city of men above ground (I think I read that on eqatlas anyway ) that I can adventure too.   The buildings look great, the sounds are perfect! Very very nice touch indeed!<br>
<br>
I can't wait to get home and explore this city more and seek out some quests.<br>
<br>
<br>
The Deep<br>
<br>
My first level 50-60 dungeon experience in Luclin. This is an &quot;abyss&quot; of sorts off of the echo caverns, and seems to lead directly to the center of Luclin. RUMORS of Luclin herself being somewhere in the center of the moon make me wanna see the ends of this zone. Everything from the zone in on was blue to a level 60.  It takes about 2 minutes to get here from Shadow Haven through Echo Caverns.<br>
<br>
Jury's still out here.  My group was me (56 cleric), 1 60 monk, 1 54 monk, 1 49 monk (only one without epic), and a 59 pally and 54 mage.  No crowd control, but we were okay. The shrooms are annoying because they slow/stun and seem to have a nasty &quot;dot&quot; of sorts that turns who they are fighting into a giant mushroom for a few seconds. They cast spells, but are not a &quot;class&quot; of sorts in that they seem to only be able to cast &quot;mushroom slow&quot; and &quot;mushroom stun&quot; and such. But at the same time, they are not proccing, they are casting.  I don't know if other mobs have individual spells rather than just individual procs.  In any case its a neat touch! <br>
<br>
If we had an add, I was able to tank it (wow thanks to new buff spells I have 2963 hp and 975 AC self buffed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). With singles I chain stunned which made the shrooms only try to hit me and slow me (who cares if I was slowed).<br>
<br>
The exp was very good here, noticeable movement in both skills and normal level exp in just 2 hours with a 20/80 split.<br>
<br>
THE LOOT BITES MY GRANNY'S BUM though, at least near the zone. If you think we were going much deeper than zone in without a chanter/bard you are a crazy person.<br>
<br>
The TRAINS were godawful.  I mean Blackburrow type 20 mobs at once to the zone and they happened a lot, and these things coming from deeper in were not not not friendly. The mix of 20 shrooms, giant armored beetle/crab things, and zombie men (all entralled) was a sight to behold.  Agro radius seemed fairly large fro the beetles and fairly small for the shrooms.<br>
<br>
Anyway, thats my take so far.<br>
<br>
AD<br>
